    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.24.10-11_0001"/>

                <note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">10</fw>                
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        1568 Kappa &#35; 9
                        Stadium Village
                        Salt Lake City, Utah
                        3 July 1956
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim Farm, Rt. 6</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I want to thank you for your letter and for the suggestions that you made which will be of assistance to me in writing my thesis. The library here has sent for the two theses which you felt might be of help. There is, however, one further bit of assistance that I would like. I would be very appreciative if you would send me a photograph of yourself that I can have copied for the frontispiece of my thesis. I would return the photograph as soon as the re-prints were made.</p>
                
                <p>I have been very much interested in your poetry since first becoming acquainted with "Hugh Glass" at a country high school at Cornell, Nebraska. I have read and enjoyed all of your published prose works and all of your poetry that I have found copies of. I still include the Song of Three Friends, The Song of Hugh Glass, and The Song of the Indian Wars in the English courses that I teach at Scottsbluff, Nebraska, where I have been teaching in the high-school for the past eight years.</p>
                
                <p>Thank you again for your interest.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                    <signed>Ray A. Frakes</signed>
                    <signed>Ray A. Frakes</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
